summary:
Arya :  Jaqen kissed me!
Sansa : What!
Arya : I've got to tell Gendry. I can't tell Gendry ! I didn't even do anything wrong!...
body:
Arya :  Jaqen kissed me!
Sansa : What!
Arya : I've got to tell Gendry. I can't tell Gendry ! I didn't even do anything wrong! Jaqen kissed *me*; I didn't even kiss him back! Okay, fine! I kissed him back! Is that what you want me to say?
Sansa : I literally haven't said a word for, like, over an hour.
Arya : And now he won't even talk to me! 'Cause I saw him this morning and he just panicked, changed his face and walked away from me.
Sansa : He what?
Arya : He does that sometimes. And then... Ha! Jaqen just... He just... He just...
Sansa : Kisses you.
Arya : Stupid Jaqen H'ghar !
Sansa : How was it? Was it...?
Arya : I was like Scarlett O'Hara in my freaking curtain dress.
Sansa : Yeah, but *how* did he do it?
Arya : He just, like, grabbed me. And he just took me. I mean, he was a man and I was a girl. It was firm, but tender.
Sansa :  Damn.
Arya : Yeah I saw through space and time for a minute but that's not the point!

title: Keys to the North
body:
Unpopular opinion here but i think there is more than one key to the North. I think that while all four of the remaining Stark children (and Jon) have varying degrees of likelihood of inheritance all of them are important. 

  • Arya’s name was used to secure Bolton rule and at the same time was used to spark rebellion with the mountain clans who were fighting to get back “the Valiant Ned’s little girl”.
  • Bran is the rightful heir unless Robb’s will is found and is actually enacted. 
  • Sansa would have rights after Bran and Rickon. Depending on what happens in the Vale she would have the lords of the Vale to back her.  
  • Wyman Manderly would not have sent Davos to find Rickon if he was not considered important. Rickon would be next in line to inherit after Bran. 

All of the remaining Stark children will play a role in reclaiming the North and all are important in their own ways.

summary: You know what we should do? We should do one of those modern adaptation video diaries? Like the Lizzie Bennet Diaries but the...
body:
You know what we should do? We should do one of those modern adaptation video diaries? Like the Lizzie Bennet Diaries but the Arya Stark Diaries. It’s cheap, its simple, and we could make an accurate adaptation of her character. But it will be set in the asoiaf universe but instead of talking to the audience, she would actually be talking to Bloodraven, which would explain why she is talking to a camera in a pre-historic universe. 


….I am supposed to be studying for my Histology exam but i am procrastinating. Can you tell? :B
